{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop the deduction of carers allowance from people's Universal Credit award",
        "additional_details": "As a carer I am only able to work on a part time basis, due to my caring commitments. However, I find myself, as many others can, worse off. I receive less than \u00a3100 a week in carers allowance and then Universal Credit take it all back off me in a monthly sum. When you take into consideration the amount carers save the government by providing care, I believe this is very unfair.",
        "background": "Stop the deduction of Carers Allowance from the carers Universal Credit award, it shouldn\u2019t be treated as an income.",
